{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In the original Ng et al. 's conceptualization 18, creation and evaluation of AI are core components of AI literacy.",
    "MAILS 42 drawing from the Ng et al. 's conceptualization 18 identified creation of AI as a related, but separate construct from AI literacy.",
    "AILQ 35, on the other hand, drawing from the same conceptualization includes creating AI as a core part of AI literacy.",
    "Several other scales also consider the ability to critically evaluate AI as a core part of AI literacy [32] [33] [34] 36, 38, 44.",
    "Considering the widespread integration of AI into daily and professional life, a question arises, whether the skills to create and critically evaluate AI will not have to be included as core competencies of AI literacy in near future, as those competencies might be crucial for functional AI literacy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
